The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Briefs
                                                                                                               SPORT BRIEFS
                  
	Dhaka: Bangladesh left-arm spinner Abdur Razzak has been cleared of having a suspect bowling action by the International Cricket Council (ICC), Bangladesh Cricket Board (BCB) said on Thursday.    
	The ICC banned Razzak from bowling after he was reported by the elite panel umpires Daryl Harper and Ashoka de Silva after the home series against New Zealand in October.    
	His stock delivery and faster ball are now within the ICC tolerance level of 15 and his action was now legal, the BCB said in a statement. As a result the previous suspension has been lifted.        
	Calcutta: Australian fast bowler Mitchell Johnson joined South African speedster Dale Steyn in second place in the ICCs Test ranking for bowlers following his 4/115 in the second Test in Durban.    
